    &gt; 
    &gt; 
    &gt; assertTrue(true) is meaningless and confusing. By 
    &gt; default, if you get to
    &gt; point X of a test, then all must be well so far, 
    &gt; otherwise the next line
    &gt; will be &quot;fail(...)&quot;. Don&#39;t write assertTrue(true). :)
    &gt; 
    &gt; Let the framework communicate; it&#39;s a good one!
